    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">ROI Examples for Swansea Businesses</h2>

    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Prices on a page only mean something when you can see what they deliver in the real world. Here are two scenarios showing what SEO investment looks like for actual Swansea businesses.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-3">Mumbles Restaurant: 50 Extra Covers Per Month</h3>

    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">A seafood restaurant on Mumbles Road was relying entirely on walk-ins and TripAdvisor. Their Google Business Profile was barely filled in and their website sat on page three for "restaurant Mumbles" and "seafood Swansea." On the Starter plan at £497 per month, we optimised their Google Business Profile, built local citations, and went after five high-intent keywords including "best restaurant Mumbles" and "seafood restaurant Swansea Bay."</p>

    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Within four months, they were showing in the local map pack for all five keywords. Online reservations jumped by 50 covers per month, worth roughly £1,250 in extra revenue at £25 per head. That is a 2.5x return on a £497 monthly spend, and the results keep compounding as domain authority grows.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-3">Morriston Trades Business: 20 New Leads Per Month</h3>

    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">A plumbing and heating company based near <strong>Morriston Hospital</strong> was spending £800 a month on Google Ads with patchy results. They switched to the Growth plan at £997 per month. We targeted 15 keywords covering emergency plumbing, boiler installation, and heating services across Swansea postcodes, and built location-specific service pages for <strong>SA1 Waterfront</strong>, Sketty, Uplands, and Gorseinon.</p>

    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">By month five, organic traffic had climbed 340 percent. The business now picks up an average of 20 qualified leads a month through organic search, each worth between £150 and £3,000 depending on the job. Even at a conservative average job value of £500 with a 30 percent close rate, that is £3,000 per month in new revenue from a £997 investment. Unlike paid ads, these rankings keep delivering leads without ongoing click costs.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">Swansea vs Cardiff vs Bristol: SEO Pricing Comparison</h2>

    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Swansea businesses benefit from a pricing advantage that Cardiff and Bristol simply do not have. Here is how typical monthly SEO retainers stack up across the three cities.</p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
      <table class="w-full border-collapse text-left">
